{
  "text": "The stages were calibrated by a set of synthetic fluid inclusions with an estimated accuracy of about AE0\u00c118C at the triple point of CO 2 (\u00c056\u00c168C), at the triple point of H 2 O (0\u00c10158C), and at the critical temperature of H 2 O (3748C). Freezing temperature (T f ), eutectic temperature (T e ), final melting temperature (T m ), and homogenization temperature (T h ) were measured during heating^freezing cycles. Heating rates were 0\u00c118C/min approaching T m , and 0\u00c158C/min approaching T h . Microthermometric data to obtain fluid inclusion compositions, densities, and isochores were processed with the software packages FLUID 1 [CITATION_1] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
